Yes, that is the default behaviour of the GridBagLayout. If you don&#39;t like that then you can use a different layout manager on the frame. Read the tutorial on [Layout Managers](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/layout/visual.html). The easiest might be the `FlowLayout`. You can specify the alignment to be left aligned.

&gt; with dimensions say 50x50.

